= Ramón Danzós Palomino

*Corriente: los ortodoxos. Cada consejo suyo fortalece a su corriente — y las otras participan menos.*

A campesino from Sonora who has been, in one lifetime, cotton picker, union man, political prisoner, and — in 1964, on the ticket of a front the government refused to register — the first communist candidate for President of the Republic since the war. He campaigned in huaraches through valleys where the candidate of the PRI arrived by plane, and lost officially by one hundred percent to nothing. The ejidos remember him. So does the DFS.

